						<summary>

						<p>This records a gift of 2 <hi rend="italic">kaḻañju</hi> and 2 <hi rend="italic">mā</hi> of gold made by Baṭṭaṉ Araṅgaṉ <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> Śivacharaṇa-toṇḍan ‘a devotee of Tiruviśalūr’ to provide for <hi rend="italic">śidāri</hi> incense being waved before (the image of) Pichchadēvar (Bhikshāṭana) during the three services in the temple. </p>						

